		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Zepper wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I was thinking about getting a Game Genie. Would it work in a NES + Famicom cart, without codes? <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /></div><br /><br />I don't remember, but you can test for yourself. Plug in the game genie with no game. if the NES resets itself every second like when there is no cartridge, then no, it won't work. If it stays on, then you are fine.<br /><br />I am assuming this question pertains to the presence of the lockout IC present in a standard cartridge and the gyromite-style embedded adapter (which most adapters will not have a suitable solution for).

		

